268
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:17,196
I'm home!

269
00:13:23,669 --> 00:13:25,437
I'm home.

270
00:13:25,504 --> 00:13:27,807
What? Everyone's here?

271
00:13:27,873 --> 00:13:29,041
Oh, yes.

272
00:13:31,243 --> 00:13:33,813
-Come in, Sally!
-Huh?

273
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:37,016
Hello.

274
00:13:37,082 --> 00:13:39,351
She's my lover, Saori Itoh.

275
00:13:43,522 --> 00:13:44,390
Hi.

276
00:13:45,391 --> 00:13:47,860
"Sally" is that "Sally"?

277
00:13:47,927 --> 00:13:50,062
How old are you, exactly?

278
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:52,231
I'm 23.

279
00:13:57,269 --> 00:14:00,906
<i>LONG LOST LOVE</i>

280
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:04,910
<i>PARADISE LOST</i> - JUNICHI WATANABE

281
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:06,412
<i>UNTIL THIS LIFE ENDS</i>

282
00:14:06,478 --> 00:14:09,148
<i>THE END OF THIS LOVE</i>

283
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:14,520
What is love?

284
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,121
Don't tell him!

285
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:17,289
What?

286
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:21,527
Please. I need to tell him myself.

287
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,096
Soseki doesn't know?

288
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:25,231
Not yet.

289
00:14:26,398 --> 00:14:29,501
Does Shunichiro know that
you dated Soseki?

290
00:14:30,302 --> 00:14:31,403
He knows everything.

291
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:33,205
Okay.

292
00:14:37,643 --> 00:14:40,646
With these things, timing is everything.

293
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:45,718
I stopped coming home, calling him

294
00:14:45,784 --> 00:14:48,053
and tracking his phone location.

295
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,855
Once he starts getting the hint,

296
00:14:50,456 --> 00:14:53,392
that's when I break it to him.

297
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:55,828
If I tell him before, he'll get pissed.

298
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:57,696
It would be dramatic!

299
00:14:58,230 --> 00:14:59,398
Which step are you in now?

300
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:02,034
Around the "the" of

301
00:15:02,101 --> 00:15:05,671
"getting the hint."

302
00:15:06,205 --> 00:15:09,875
People start giving up
with the passing of time.

303
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:13,545
You're so experienced, Sally.

304
00:15:14,146 --> 00:15:16,949
It's a big shock
when you hear it from others.

305
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:19,351
Don't tell him, please!

306
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:23,889
I understand. I'm a romance beginner,
I'll do what you say.

307
00:15:25,891 --> 00:15:27,726
Good girl.

308
00:15:31,864 --> 00:15:34,800
But you loved him so much.

309
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,305
You know,

310
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:42,041
I want to be happy.

311
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:43,976
What?

312
00:15:44,043 --> 00:15:46,078
I'm sure you know, Sora.

313
00:15:46,145 --> 00:15:50,749
<i>But when I'm with Soseki,</i>
<i>I turn into a crazy stalker.</i>

314
00:15:50,816 --> 00:15:52,518
<i>I felt only pain.</i>

315
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:55,354
<i>That's not happy love.</i>

316
00:15:56,121 --> 00:16:00,125
But when I'm with Shunichiro,

317
00:16:00,192 --> 00:16:02,428
I'm not in pain.

318
00:16:03,829 --> 00:16:06,598
I feel soft and fluffy,

319
00:16:07,199 --> 00:16:09,301
like I'm sleeping on top of a cloud.

320
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:14,640
But isn't love supposed to be painful?

321
00:16:15,607 --> 00:16:17,176
That's my guess, at least.

322
00:16:17,776 --> 00:16:18,844
What?

323
00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:23,248
In that case, Soseki will be single.

324
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:25,117
He could date Mom now!

325
00:16:26,352 --> 00:16:28,620
What the hell! Is that what's happening?

326
00:16:28,687 --> 00:16:33,258
Your voice sounded a bit rough there.
Don't burn our house down, okay?

327
00:16:34,259 --> 00:16:35,260
Oh, right.

328
00:16:36,161 --> 00:16:38,130
I'll find my own happiness.

329
00:16:38,864 --> 00:16:40,332
I don't care about Soseki anymore.

330
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:43,168
<i>If this love is over</i>

331
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:46,005
<i>It's like it never existed</i>

332
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:47,339
Alright.

333
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:53,979
-Excuse me, can I get another?
-Yes.

334
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,415
Could I?

335
00:16:57,616 --> 00:16:58,784
I'll have the same.

336
00:16:58,851 --> 00:16:59,952
Yes, ma'am.

337
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:04,323
I'll call Mom. She'll worry.

338
00:17:06,959 --> 00:17:09,528
You and your mom are so close.

339
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:11,797
It's normal, right?

340
00:17:13,132 --> 00:17:14,933
You don't know.

341
00:17:15,667 --> 00:17:18,771
You think all mothers and daughters
are like you guys.

342
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:20,773
Am I wrong?

343
00:17:21,507 --> 00:17:24,376
I have a really toxic mom.

344
00:17:28,981 --> 00:17:30,682
She's so terrible.

345
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:34,520
Maybe it's my mom's fault that I chase men

346
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:36,321
all the time.

347
00:17:38,957 --> 00:17:41,760
Ever since I was little,

348
00:17:42,294 --> 00:17:44,863
I never felt loved by my mom.

349
00:17:44,930 --> 00:17:48,267
Not even once.

350
00:17:49,034 --> 00:17:50,202
Really?

351
00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:53,939
I…

352
00:17:56,508 --> 00:17:58,911
I can't trust women.

353
00:17:58,977 --> 00:18:01,613
I don't need women in my life.

354
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:08,253
You should trust women.

355
00:18:09,121 --> 00:18:11,723
I'm sure there are women you can trust.

356
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:16,261
In that case,

357
00:18:17,729 --> 00:18:20,299
can I trust you?

358
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:22,367
Sure.

359
00:18:23,402 --> 00:18:25,037
Will you be my friend?

360
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:28,907
If you'll have me.

361
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:42,054
I see. You became friends?

362
00:18:42,721 --> 00:18:43,689
Yeah.

363
00:18:44,356 --> 00:18:46,658
-That's a great thing.
-Yeah.

364
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:49,561
Everyone has their issues, huh?

365
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:53,132
They do? Is that what you talked about?

366
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,702
Issues with her family.

367
00:18:56,768 --> 00:18:57,970
Oh, that?

368
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:01,907
We're happy.

369
00:19:03,709 --> 00:19:06,145
<i>If this love is over</i>

370
00:19:08,247 --> 00:19:10,949
<i>It's like it never existed</i>

371
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:16,221
<i>A brooch that lost its clasp</i>

372
00:19:16,288 --> 00:19:18,991
<i>I have to throw it out</i>

373
00:19:19,725 --> 00:19:21,059
That's what she said.

374
00:19:21,126 --> 00:19:22,761
Sally was singing that.

375
00:19:25,531 --> 00:19:27,332
Love ends, huh?

376
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:29,835
Yeah.

377
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:34,406
Maybe it's beautiful because it ends.

378
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,075
But…

379
00:19:41,613 --> 00:19:43,916
Parent-and-kid relationships don't end.

380
00:19:45,751 --> 00:19:47,519
And friendships don't end.

381
00:19:50,622 --> 00:19:52,691
Relationships that don't end are nice.

382
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:56,762
What if you get married?

383
00:19:56,828 --> 00:19:58,630
Then men and women don't end either.

384
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:01,333
One in three couples get divorced.

385
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:05,771
But we don't hear one in three children
cutting off ties with their parents.

386
00:20:06,338 --> 00:20:07,706
I see.

387
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:09,942
We're the strongest!

388
00:20:10,475 --> 00:20:11,743
Hug!

389
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:14,813
-Ouch!
-A Sleeper Hold!

390
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,715
I yield!

391
00:20:16,782 --> 00:20:19,751
What's wrong? Why are you this energetic?

392
00:20:23,155 --> 00:20:26,291
I have my date tomorrow.
I'm so nervous, I'll go crazy!

393
00:20:26,358 --> 00:20:29,094
I'm so scared that I want to
throw an uppercut!

394
00:20:29,161 --> 00:20:30,462
Stop it!

395
00:20:30,529 --> 00:20:32,264
Oh, with Doctor Wataru?

396
00:20:32,331 --> 00:20:34,733
A real date, without nose hair.

397
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:38,403
Will you go on another date with me?

398
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:41,773
The date you won back from him!

399
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,542
I'm so nervous, I can't sleep!

400
00:20:43,609 --> 00:20:47,646
Mom, go on the date for me!

401
00:20:47,713 --> 00:20:48,780
That's impossible.

402
00:20:48,847 --> 00:20:50,849
I'm so pathetic!

403
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,018
You're not pathetic!

404
00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:55,921
I'm the most proud of you.

405
00:20:55,988 --> 00:20:58,724
You're the best daughter in the world!

406
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:00,125
Are you drunk?

407
00:21:00,192 --> 00:21:02,194
Be confident, Sora!

408
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,230
When you were born, I almost gave you

409
00:21:05,297 --> 00:21:06,765
The Cutest In The World Award!

410
00:21:06,832 --> 00:21:08,267
What is that?

411
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:11,637
Before that, The Cutest
In The World Award was mine.

412
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:14,406
Two generations of award winners!

413
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:16,742
First generation!

414
00:21:16,808 --> 00:21:17,676
Second generation!

415
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:57,115
REGISTRATION CERTIFICATE

416
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:06,625
UMBILICAL CORD, BABY HAIR

417
00:22:15,967 --> 00:22:17,469
Umbilical cord…

418
00:22:33,085 --> 00:22:34,086
Sorry.

419
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:39,157
I was about to leave and my client,
Mr. Yoshida said his back gave out.

420
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:41,860
Is he okay?

421
00:22:41,927 --> 00:22:44,429
It wasn't serious. Let's go.

422
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:46,765
Okay.

423
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,802
You want popcorn?

424
00:22:50,869 --> 00:22:51,870
Yeah.

425
00:22:51,937 --> 00:22:53,438
Here's your order.

426
00:22:56,208 --> 00:23:00,579
<i>ISEKAI WONDER</i>

427
00:23:16,828 --> 00:23:17,829
Are you okay?

428
00:23:17,896 --> 00:23:20,031
Yeah. Oops.

429
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:43,155
That's weird. I can't turn.

430
00:23:44,723 --> 00:23:45,924
I'm sorry!

431
00:23:47,692 --> 00:23:48,727
Wow.

432
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:50,996
Your legs are too long!

433
00:23:52,564 --> 00:23:53,999
I'm too tall.

434
00:23:55,233 --> 00:23:56,334
I'll work hard too.

435
00:23:56,902 --> 00:23:59,671
One, two, one, two.

436
00:24:00,505 --> 00:24:01,373
What would you like?

437
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:04,676
I'll have the ginger ale, please.

438
00:24:04,743 --> 00:24:05,911
One ginger ale.

439
00:24:05,977 --> 00:24:07,579
You're not eating?

440
00:24:07,646 --> 00:24:10,081
You eat. I'm not hungry.

441
00:24:11,216 --> 00:24:12,184
Let's see…

442
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:14,986
<i>It's so fun, but I'm also</i>
<i>so nervous that I can't eat!</i>

443
00:24:15,821 --> 00:24:17,689
<i>Help me, Mom!</i>

444
00:24:18,256 --> 00:24:21,593
<i>LONG LOST LOVE</i>

445
00:24:32,637 --> 00:24:33,805
Ouch!

446
00:24:36,274 --> 00:24:39,478
I am alive.

447
00:24:50,088 --> 00:24:51,356
<i>BLUE LOVE</i>

448
00:25:03,768 --> 00:25:05,036
AOI MINASE IS TALENTED! BY GON

449
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:06,438
I'LL WRITE A MASTERPIECE AND GET RICH!

450
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:07,439
WRITE! DON'T GET LOST!

451
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:09,040
Alright.

452
00:25:10,075 --> 00:25:12,544
What are you doing?

453
00:25:12,611 --> 00:25:14,145
