454
00:25:14,212 --> 00:25:17,949
I haven't touched ink for a long time.
Inspiring, right?

455
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:19,918
My calligraphy's still really good.

456
00:25:19,985 --> 00:25:22,721
I wrote seven pieces, with all my heart.

457
00:25:22,787 --> 00:25:25,590
Call me if you're coming. I'm not dressed!

458
00:25:25,657 --> 00:25:27,492
Your phone was off.

459
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:29,194
Oh, I turn it off when I'm writing.

460
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:30,228
You're not writing.

461
00:25:31,796 --> 00:25:33,732
Don't say that!

462
00:25:33,798 --> 00:25:35,934
"Break up? That's what you say
to a geisha.

463
00:25:36,001 --> 00:25:39,170
For now, tell me to die!"

464
00:25:39,237 --> 00:25:41,706
-What?
-Isn't that how the quote goes?

465
00:25:41,773 --> 00:25:44,409
What's going on in that head of yours?

466
00:25:44,476 --> 00:25:46,945
What two ideas are you connecting?

467
00:25:47,012 --> 00:25:48,246
Why are you here, anyways?

468
00:25:48,813 --> 00:25:53,184
You said you couldn't write or think of
any ideas. I was worried about you.

469
00:25:53,251 --> 00:25:55,220
Where's the <i>taiyaki?</i>
<i>Sanmayaki</i> is fine too.

470
00:25:55,287 --> 00:25:56,388
You brought snacks, right?

471
00:25:56,454 --> 00:25:57,656
You…

472
00:25:58,523 --> 00:25:59,691
I brought you these!

473
00:25:59,758 --> 00:26:02,127
Ew! Where's the sugar?

474
00:26:02,193 --> 00:26:03,962
I want sweets!

475
00:26:04,029 --> 00:26:05,397
Lick some sugar cubes!

476
00:26:05,463 --> 00:26:07,265
-I'm not a horse!
-Hey.

477
00:26:08,833 --> 00:26:12,704
I have something serious
I want to talk to you about.

478
00:26:24,683 --> 00:26:26,217
<i>Mom's secret technique!</i>

479
00:26:26,284 --> 00:26:29,087
Say, "I forgot my gloves!
My hands are cold!"

480
00:26:29,154 --> 00:26:32,557
And put your hands in their coat pocket.

481
00:26:34,559 --> 00:26:35,827
Hands…

482
00:26:36,461 --> 00:26:37,295
Hands?

483
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:40,532
I forgot my gloves.

484
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:42,601
Where? In that boat?

485
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:44,436
No, not there.

486
00:26:45,236 --> 00:26:47,606
-I left them at home.
-I see.

487
00:26:49,908 --> 00:26:51,276
My hands are cold.

488
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:54,012
I'm sure they are.

489
00:26:54,679 --> 00:26:57,716
It's winter, after all.

490
00:27:01,186 --> 00:27:02,520
I have pockets though.

491
00:27:03,388 --> 00:27:04,456
My own pockets.

492
00:27:13,665 --> 00:27:15,133
-Sorry.
-Sure.

493
00:27:18,336 --> 00:27:20,171
HIKARU IRINO

494
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:24,609
Hello?

495
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:29,714
Why do you sound like
the person you hate most called you?

496
00:27:29,781 --> 00:27:31,549
Well, you're not wrong.

497
00:27:32,717 --> 00:27:33,652
Should I hang up?

498
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:36,121
-I'm on my date.
-What?

499
00:27:36,187 --> 00:27:37,689
My date!

500
00:27:41,860 --> 00:27:42,861
Is it going well?

501
00:27:42,927 --> 00:27:44,362
Very well.

502
00:27:44,863 --> 00:27:45,697
<i>I see.</i>

503
00:27:46,531 --> 00:27:47,599
<i>Don't mess up.</i>

504
00:27:48,466 --> 00:27:50,168
What did you want to talk about?

505
00:27:50,235 --> 00:27:52,070
I'll tell you later.

506
00:27:56,775 --> 00:27:57,776
Whatever.

507
00:28:01,613 --> 00:28:03,982
I thought it would be cute

508
00:28:04,049 --> 00:28:07,552
if we put ears on Jadwiga.

509
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:11,956
I'm so bad at drawing!

510
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:18,263
Shunichiro's been peppy again

511
00:28:18,329 --> 00:28:21,866
since this morning.
He has a date with Sally.

512
00:28:21,933 --> 00:28:23,635
No one says "peppy" anymore!

513
00:28:23,702 --> 00:28:27,205
If I keep talking to you, I can
never write anything modern!

514
00:28:27,272 --> 00:28:29,641
He's been changing outfits
since this morning.

515
00:28:29,708 --> 00:28:31,743
He went through so many.

516
00:28:36,981 --> 00:28:39,784
Asking, "Which one makes me look
the most handsome?"

517
00:28:39,851 --> 00:28:42,620
But she was really cute.

518
00:28:42,687 --> 00:28:46,725
I totally lost to him. Even if I could
marry Aoba, she's 26.

519
00:28:46,791 --> 00:28:49,027
-Sally's 23!
-23.

520
00:28:49,094 --> 00:28:51,362
And you didn't marry Aoba.

521
00:28:51,429 --> 00:28:52,397
Geez.

522
00:28:52,464 --> 00:28:54,866
That doesn't matter.

523
00:28:54,933 --> 00:28:56,601
I heard from Dad.

524
00:28:56,668 --> 00:29:00,004
She was originally
your editor's girlfriend, right?

525
00:29:00,071 --> 00:29:00,905
Yes.

526
00:29:00,972 --> 00:29:03,808
-Then, she switched over to Dad.
-Yup.

527
00:29:03,875 --> 00:29:05,543
It was impressive.

528
00:29:05,610 --> 00:29:06,945
Is she okay?

529
00:29:07,011 --> 00:29:08,613
What do you mean?

530
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:12,617
You know, for example… Could she be…

531
00:29:14,185 --> 00:29:15,019
after the money?

532
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:18,056
No, I don't think so at all.

533
00:29:18,123 --> 00:29:19,424
She's not the type.

534
00:29:19,991 --> 00:29:21,192
You think?

535
00:29:21,259 --> 00:29:23,661
You want assurance
that everything will work out.

536
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:25,864
-But I'm not so sure.
-What?

537
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,133
Sally lives for love.

538
00:29:28,199 --> 00:29:30,401
I hope Shunichiro won't get squeezed out.

539
00:29:30,468 --> 00:29:31,469
Of money?

540
00:29:32,036 --> 00:29:34,005
Of his power to live.

541
00:29:34,072 --> 00:29:36,841
I didn't know that could be squeezed out.

542
00:29:36,908 --> 00:29:37,742
Is she a witch?

543
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:39,377
Oh, how about this?

544
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:42,113
Romance between a girl
in her early twenties starving for love,

545
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:44,582
and an old man at the end of his life.

546
00:29:44,649 --> 00:29:47,085
In the end, they end their lives together.

547
00:29:47,152 --> 00:29:50,522
-While eating duck hot pot.
-Hey, you. Don't kill my dad!

548
00:29:50,588 --> 00:29:53,625
-I'm just joking.
-Geez.

549
00:29:55,226 --> 00:29:58,863
So Sora's on her date, huh?

550
00:29:58,930 --> 00:30:01,166
She grew up fast.

551
00:30:01,699 --> 00:30:03,034
Yeah.

552
00:30:03,101 --> 00:30:04,068
Aoi.

553
00:30:05,103 --> 00:30:08,039
You love Sora. You should write about her
for your novel.

554
00:30:08,106 --> 00:30:10,642
That's a love story too.
A story about love.

555
00:30:10,708 --> 00:30:12,844
About Sora? How?

556
00:30:13,578 --> 00:30:14,913
She doesn't ask who the dad is?

557
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:16,314
Yeah.

558
00:30:16,381 --> 00:30:19,117
When she does, I use my imagination.

559
00:30:19,184 --> 00:30:22,120
I tell her he's a super famous celebrity,
or an Arab aristocrat.

560
00:30:22,187 --> 00:30:23,788
Or, I say, he wasn't Japanese!

561
00:30:23,855 --> 00:30:26,424
Is that the right response as a parent?

562
00:30:26,491 --> 00:30:28,026
Sora likes it too.

563
00:30:28,092 --> 00:30:29,594
You guys are weird.

564
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:33,832
When she was little,
that Zojirushi was her dad.

565
00:30:34,799 --> 00:30:36,935
She doesn't ask me anymore.

566
00:30:37,001 --> 00:30:39,437
She's probably no longer interested.

567
00:30:42,807 --> 00:30:44,275
You'll never tell her?

568
00:30:45,710 --> 00:30:48,780
I'll tell her one day.

569
00:30:49,747 --> 00:30:50,782
Not yet. Not now.

570
00:30:55,186 --> 00:30:56,521
Oh! I have an idea!

571
00:30:56,588 --> 00:30:57,455
What?

572
00:30:58,923 --> 00:31:00,558
I have an idea for the novel!

573
00:31:01,292 --> 00:31:02,627
-Sorry, Gon-chan, go home.
-Huh?

574
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:04,329
-I can't work with you around.
-What?

575
00:31:04,395 --> 00:31:05,563
Sorry. Go home.

576
00:31:06,831 --> 00:31:08,466
Sorry for making you walk.

577
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:09,467
It's fine.

578
00:31:11,336 --> 00:31:12,337
What should we eat tonight?

579
00:31:13,838 --> 00:31:14,873
What?

580
00:31:14,939 --> 00:31:16,641
If you go eat Italian,

581
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:18,977
have tiramisu for dessert.
Tiramisu and strawberries

582
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:21,846
are a cute girl's food!

583
00:31:23,481 --> 00:31:24,415
Tiramisu.

584
00:31:24,482 --> 00:31:26,651
Tiramisu?

585
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:29,120
Or strawberries.

586
00:31:29,187 --> 00:31:30,922
That's dessert.

587
00:31:33,992 --> 00:31:35,493
-I'm going to the restroom.
-Okay.

588
00:31:39,797 --> 00:31:41,099
Let me think.

589
00:31:41,699 --> 00:31:42,734
I don't know.

590
00:31:43,635 --> 00:31:45,470
I don't think it matters.

591
00:31:45,536 --> 00:31:47,071
That won't work!

592
00:31:47,138 --> 00:31:50,308
"I don't care" is the worst answer.
I read that online!

593
00:31:50,375 --> 00:31:52,777
That's true.

594
00:31:52,844 --> 00:31:54,579
Hey, why are you calling me?

595
00:31:55,647 --> 00:31:59,183
Mom turns off her phone
when she's writing.

596
00:32:00,218 --> 00:32:01,853
I'm second to Mom, huh?

597
00:32:02,987 --> 00:32:03,922
Do you like that?

598
00:32:03,988 --> 00:32:04,889
<i>I'm hanging up.</i>

599
00:32:04,956 --> 00:32:06,624
Wait, don't! Tell me!

600
00:32:10,728 --> 00:32:11,763
Extra-large katsudon.

601
00:32:12,597 --> 00:32:13,598
That's what you want!

602
00:32:13,665 --> 00:32:15,566
<i>With extra pickled ginger…</i>

603
00:32:15,633 --> 00:32:17,368
Wait, that's gyudon.

604
00:32:29,347 --> 00:32:30,949
This is pretty good.

605
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:43,995
This is so good!

606
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:46,998
-Are you sure this is fine?
-Huh?

607
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:49,767
I was planning to take you to
a French restaurant or something.

608
00:32:49,834 --> 00:32:51,336
But that's greasy.

609
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:55,039
I love your red bean soup
more than anything.

610
00:32:56,374 --> 00:33:00,845
How nice! You two love each other.
How wholesome.

611
00:33:00,912 --> 00:33:02,313
-We went out.
-Yes?

612
00:33:02,380 --> 00:33:04,015
To an aquarium together.

613
00:33:04,082 --> 00:33:06,351
-Wow!
-We got you a gift.

614
00:33:07,018 --> 00:33:07,885
Really?

615
00:33:07,952 --> 00:33:09,320
I'm home!

616
00:33:09,387 --> 00:33:11,322
-Welcome home!
-It's getting cold.

617
00:33:11,389 --> 00:33:12,890
Oh!

618
00:33:12,957 --> 00:33:14,359
Here's your future mom!

619
00:33:14,425 --> 00:33:15,727
What?

620
00:33:15,793 --> 00:33:18,463
I'm just kidding!

621
00:33:18,529 --> 00:33:21,032
Shunichiro.

622
00:33:21,099 --> 00:33:21,966
I'm fine with that.

623
00:33:22,033 --> 00:33:22,967
No.

624
00:33:23,034 --> 00:33:25,370
Sally, you're in your early twenties!

625
00:33:25,436 --> 00:33:28,940
He's a senior citizen.
You're really fine with that?

626
00:33:29,607 --> 00:33:31,142
Hey, Mr. Gon-chan?

627
00:33:31,209 --> 00:33:32,443
Mr. Gon-chan?

628
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:35,513
I thought Gon-chan was too friendly.

629
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:36,948
Don't say that!

630
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:40,051
Just call him Gon.
Honestly, "Go" is enough.

631
00:33:40,118 --> 00:33:40,952
"Gon-chan," please.

632
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:44,188
In that case, Gon-chan.

633
00:33:45,923 --> 00:33:47,358
What are you smiling about?

634
00:33:48,559 --> 00:33:51,529
You know, ever since I met Shunichiro,

635
00:33:51,596 --> 00:33:52,597
I can sleep.

636
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:56,067
I can sleep really well at night,

637
00:33:56,934 --> 00:33:59,537
and the world feels warmer.

638
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:03,674
I feel safe now.

639
00:34:04,242 --> 00:34:05,777
I feel safe that I'm alive.

640
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:09,747
That you're alive? That's deep.

641
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:15,720
I felt like the ground was always
shaking beneath me.

642
00:34:17,188 --> 00:34:18,456
But now, I'm alright.

643
00:34:19,323 --> 00:34:20,458
I see.

644
00:34:20,525 --> 00:34:22,894
I found an apartment,

645
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:25,963
and I found a new job too.

646
00:34:26,030 --> 00:34:29,434
Shunichiro, you rented
that apartment, right?

647
00:34:30,968 --> 00:34:33,971
You can pay me back whenever.

648
00:34:36,307 --> 00:34:38,142
I'll work and pay you back.

649
00:34:43,114 --> 00:34:44,248
I took a look.

650
00:34:44,949 --> 00:34:45,917
What do you think?

651
00:34:48,152 --> 00:34:49,120
I think it's great!

652
00:34:52,023 --> 00:34:53,357
I wrote it in two hours.

653
00:34:53,424 --> 00:34:55,126
That's impressive.

654
00:34:55,193 --> 00:34:58,463
I just wrote the main plot.
I had the idea during the day.

655
00:34:58,529 --> 00:35:01,199
This is about a mother
and daughter, right?

656
00:35:01,265 --> 00:35:03,801
Right. That's the problem.

657
00:35:03,868 --> 00:35:05,903
It's not a romance novel.

658
00:35:05,970 --> 00:35:08,206
<i>Let's pitch this.</i>

659
00:35:08,272 --> 00:35:09,107
What?

660
00:35:09,674 --> 00:35:11,676
I'll make sure this pitch goes through.

661
00:35:12,343 --> 00:35:13,811
I want to read this novel

662
00:35:14,545 --> 00:35:15,913
more than anyone!

663
00:35:24,822 --> 00:35:25,823
Try it on.

664
00:35:26,757 --> 00:35:28,426
-What?
-That hat.

665
00:35:34,398 --> 00:35:35,399
It's cute.

666
00:35:36,534 --> 00:35:37,568
Huh?

667
00:35:38,136 --> 00:35:39,237
Can I buy it for you?

668
00:35:40,471 --> 00:35:41,506
Huh?

669
00:35:43,074 --> 00:35:44,442
No.

670
00:35:45,176 --> 00:35:46,444
I don't need it.

671
00:35:46,511 --> 00:35:48,312
32,600 YEN

672
00:35:50,381 --> 00:35:51,983
Can you wait a second?

673
00:35:53,684 --> 00:35:56,787
It's a designer brand. I'm going to go
withdraw some money at the ATM.

674
00:35:56,854 --> 00:35:58,222
No, I don't want it.

675
00:36:01,259 --> 00:36:03,628
You calling me cute, that was enough.

676
00:36:06,197 --> 00:36:07,532
It made me happy.

677
00:36:11,269 --> 00:36:12,670
To be honest,

678
00:36:13,938 --> 00:36:16,607
I'm not used to going on dates with girls.

679
00:36:17,942 --> 00:36:19,010
Yeah.

680
00:36:19,076 --> 00:36:21,979
So I don't know about how much
money to spend. I'm sorry.

681
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:24,215
It's fine.

682
00:36:24,282 --> 00:36:26,150
I'm bad at rowing the swan boat too.

683
00:36:26,217 --> 00:36:28,686
I asked you to do that.

684
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:31,689
But the next spot is pretty good.

685
00:36:31,756 --> 00:36:34,492
My <i>senpai</i> took me there once.

686
00:36:48,239 --> 00:36:50,841
You said tiramisu and strawberries.
So I chose Italian.

687
00:36:51,475 --> 00:36:54,345
What a pretty restaurant.
I didn't know about this place.

688
00:36:55,379 --> 00:36:59,350
What should we get? We don't need to
get a course. We can get à la carte.

689
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:01,752
It's pretty affordable.

690
00:37:02,453 --> 00:37:03,487
So don't worry…

691
00:37:06,891 --> 00:37:08,192
What's wrong, Sora?

692
00:37:10,962 --> 00:37:12,763
My stomach hurts.

693
00:37:12,830 --> 00:37:14,031
What?

694
00:37:15,666 --> 00:37:16,667
Are you okay?

695
00:37:17,468 --> 00:37:20,571
I'm sorry. I can walk on my own.

696
00:37:21,372 --> 00:37:22,707
Should we get a taxi?

697
00:37:23,441 --> 00:37:25,343
I might get sick.

698
00:37:26,077 --> 00:37:28,913
Sorry for making you drink.

699
00:37:28,980 --> 00:37:30,214
It's fine.

700
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:35,753
Here.

701
00:37:36,954 --> 00:37:37,822
What?

702
00:37:37,888 --> 00:37:39,657
We're not far from TaiyouDo.

703
00:37:40,424 --> 00:37:42,260
-No.
-It's fine.

704
00:37:42,326 --> 00:37:45,062
I'm not tall for nothing. Come.

705
00:37:48,666 --> 00:37:49,734
This is embarrassing.

706
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:51,269
Not the time to be embarrassed.

707
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:53,537
What are we doing at TaiyouDo?

708
00:37:53,604 --> 00:37:55,139
Leave it to me.

709
00:37:55,206 --> 00:37:57,241
Right. You're a chiropractor.

710
00:37:58,309 --> 00:37:59,377
I'm a professional.

711
00:38:01,145 --> 00:38:02,346
To tell you the truth,

712
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:06,250
my stomach was hurting a little
the whole time.

713
00:38:06,317 --> 00:38:07,785
You should've told me!

714
00:38:08,519 --> 00:38:11,722
I was nervous for my very first date

715
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:13,190
in my life.

716
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:18,663
You're not counting the nose hair date
from the other day?

717
00:38:21,799 --> 00:38:22,633
Sorry.

718
00:38:23,901 --> 00:38:25,836
TAIYOUDO

719
00:38:31,442 --> 00:38:32,376
Sorry about this.

720
00:38:36,981 --> 00:38:39,083
I'm even more nervous now.

721
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:43,821
Forget that it's me. Pretend I'm your mom.

722
00:38:51,228 --> 00:38:54,098
<i>Mom's patting was so fast.</i>

723
00:38:55,433 --> 00:38:57,068
It wasn't really relaxing.

724
00:38:57,134 --> 00:38:58,135
What?

725
00:38:59,136 --> 00:39:00,404
If I knew this would happen,

726
00:39:01,238 --> 00:39:04,041
I would've asked you to wear
the nose hair again.

727
00:39:06,610 --> 00:39:10,247
Close your eyes.
Take a deep breath and relax.

728
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:27,431
You're right. It doesn't hurt
as much anymore.

729
00:39:28,099 --> 00:39:31,102
Right? I may not look it,
but I'm pretty good.

730
00:39:32,069 --> 00:39:35,239
I know.

731
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:37,174
Everyone in town comes here.

732
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:39,510
You can sleep.

733
00:39:40,644 --> 00:39:41,712
Yeah.

734
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:49,086
Sorry about the Italian restaurant.

735
00:39:49,153 --> 00:39:51,021
Don't worry about that.

736
00:39:52,523 --> 00:39:55,726
I'm sorry for not noticing
that your stomach hurt.

737
00:39:55,793 --> 00:39:56,827
I'm not very observant.

738
00:40:01,165 --> 00:40:03,334
Sora, your phone is ringing.

739
00:40:04,201 --> 00:40:07,671
Can you pick up, Doctor Wataru?

740
00:40:08,305 --> 00:40:10,141
It might be my mom.

741
00:40:13,177 --> 00:40:14,979
Hello?

742
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:18,949
Oh… What?

743
00:40:19,016 --> 00:40:21,552
Who is it? Sora's busy right now.

744
00:40:21,619 --> 00:40:25,756
Oh, it's nothing! I'm sorry to bother you.

745
00:40:31,662 --> 00:40:34,432
TOP 20 PERFECT RESTAURANTS
FOR YOUR FIRST DATE

746
00:40:37,501 --> 00:40:39,437
CHIROPRACTOR: TAIYOUDO

747
00:40:43,974 --> 00:40:45,242
Um…

748
00:40:46,844 --> 00:40:51,148
With this mess, there's probably
not a second date, right?

749
00:41:05,062 --> 00:41:06,931
That's my line.

750
00:41:08,098 --> 00:41:09,600
I put you in this mess.

751
00:41:10,534 --> 00:41:13,304
And you'll still try with me again
next time?

752
00:41:17,241 --> 00:41:19,143
I'll bring pain killers next time!

753
00:41:21,679 --> 00:41:26,383
I won't bring my nose hair next time.

754
00:41:26,450 --> 00:41:28,185
I want to bring my natural self.

755
00:41:33,157 --> 00:41:35,259
And two weeks passed after that.

756
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:37,962
It sounded like you two would meet
the next day.

757
00:41:38,028 --> 00:41:40,898
Right? I thought that too.

758
00:41:40,965 --> 00:41:43,701
But then, they had sports day
at Nagaiki Home…

759
00:41:43,767 --> 00:41:45,202
"Nagaiki Home"?

760
00:41:46,036 --> 00:41:47,638
A senior care center close by.

761
00:41:51,008 --> 00:41:52,943
The old people fought hard!

762
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:56,947
They wore their bodies out.
So now, TaiyouDo,

763
00:41:57,014 --> 00:41:59,884
Doctor Wataru's clinic, is really popular!

764
00:41:59,950 --> 00:42:01,919
He's really busy now.

765
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:04,421
But you're texting him, right?

766
00:42:05,022 --> 00:42:07,324
I am. I am, but…

767
00:42:07,892 --> 00:42:09,593
I can't breathe if he doesn't respond.

768
00:42:09,660 --> 00:42:10,528
Wow.

769
00:42:10,594 --> 00:42:12,796
My chest gets tight
just from seeing bunnies on TV.

770
00:42:12,863 --> 00:42:14,431
-Bunnies?
-Yeah.

771
00:42:14,999 --> 00:42:17,134
Oh, Doctor Nose Hair's
elementary school promise!

772
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:18,736
Don't call him that!

773
00:42:19,503 --> 00:42:20,337
Sorry.

774
00:42:20,404 --> 00:42:24,074
-I want my racing heart to die!
-Okay.

775
00:42:24,141 --> 00:42:25,743
I can only sleep at night.

776
00:42:25,809 --> 00:42:26,677
So you are sleeping!

777
00:42:26,744 --> 00:42:29,413
-I don't know who I am anymore!
-Oh.

778
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:32,516
I can't tell him the truth
because I don't want him to hate me.

779
00:42:32,583 --> 00:42:34,018
I haven't told him that I'm an otaku.

780
00:42:34,084 --> 00:42:36,220
I can feel myself shrinking.

781
00:42:37,588 --> 00:42:38,989
Draw, Minase!

782
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:40,624
What?

783
00:42:40,691 --> 00:42:42,793
When you're drawing, you're free.

784
00:42:42,860 --> 00:42:45,362
You won't be tied down by love.

785
00:42:51,869 --> 00:42:53,637
-I'll draw!
-Draw!

786
00:42:54,738 --> 00:42:56,540
Are Jadwiga's ears like this?

787
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:58,776
-A bit bigger.
-Okay.

788
00:42:58,842 --> 00:43:01,245
-Welcome! To go?
-Yes.

789
00:43:01,312 --> 00:43:05,249
Hey. I think we should change places.

790
00:43:05,316 --> 00:43:07,017
Wanna come over?

791
00:43:07,518 --> 00:43:08,986
Really?

792
00:43:09,053 --> 00:43:10,487
Totally fine.

793
00:43:12,189 --> 00:43:16,193
-Welcome! Come in, come on!
-Thank you for having me.

794
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:19,630
I'm so happy Sora finally
started drawing manga, thanks to you!

795
00:43:19,697 --> 00:43:20,864
It's just a hobby.

796
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:22,032
Whatever you say.

797
00:43:22,566 --> 00:43:23,901
You know,

798
00:43:23,968 --> 00:43:27,438
I want to relax in the living room.

799
00:43:28,172 --> 00:43:31,241
Can you work in your room?
Keep the door open though.

800
00:43:31,308 --> 00:43:32,543
So nothing happens.

801
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:34,445
Nothing will happen.

802
00:43:34,511 --> 00:43:35,446
Never.

803
00:43:35,512 --> 00:43:37,581
So… Irino, right?

804
00:43:37,648 --> 00:43:39,783
I'm Hikaru Irino.

805
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:43,387
What a beautiful name.
Your names mean sky and light.

806
00:43:43,454 --> 00:43:45,889
How bright!

807
00:43:45,956 --> 00:43:47,591
Your names glitter together!

808
00:43:47,658 --> 00:43:49,026
We don't use first names.

809
00:43:49,093 --> 00:43:50,728
We use last names, Mother.

810
00:43:50,794 --> 00:43:54,465
What a waste. I picked a great name
for you, Sora.

811
00:43:54,531 --> 00:43:57,468
Hikaru got his beautiful name
from his parents too!

812
00:43:59,536 --> 00:44:00,537
SANEISHA KONISHI

813
00:44:00,604 --> 00:44:02,306
Oh, this is about work.

814
00:44:02,373 --> 00:44:05,175
I'll be in my writing room.

815
00:44:05,242 --> 00:44:07,344
Make yourself at home.

816
00:44:07,411 --> 00:44:11,582
You can drink tea here. Help yourself!

817
00:44:14,752 --> 00:44:16,987
I was starting to pick up on it,

818
00:44:17,621 --> 00:44:19,657
but your mom is very free-spirited.

819
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:22,259
That's a nice way of putting it.

820
00:44:22,893 --> 00:44:26,797
Really? You're sure?

821
00:44:26,864 --> 00:44:29,700
Yeah. <i>Midsummer Skies are Dreams.</i>

822
00:44:29,767 --> 00:44:33,137
That's a great title!

823
00:44:33,203 --> 00:44:37,007
Your proposal went through.

824
00:44:37,074 --> 00:44:38,809
I'm so happy. I'll write this!

825
00:44:39,510 --> 00:44:43,380
But why are you calling me?
What about Soseki?

826
00:44:43,447 --> 00:44:46,450
I accepted the proposal, so I call you.

827
00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:48,986
That's common sense, isn't it?

828
00:44:49,053 --> 00:44:51,522
You're that type of person, Konishi.

829
00:44:51,588 --> 00:44:54,591
<i>You don't share your achievements.</i>
<i>You ask for gratitude from others.</i>

830
00:44:55,959 --> 00:44:59,530
Tachibana's out today. He has a cold.

831
00:45:00,431 --> 00:45:01,432
Oh?

832
00:45:02,232 --> 00:45:03,434
Blood type?

833
00:45:03,500 --> 00:45:05,669
Yeah. I like to write down the characters'

834
00:45:05,736 --> 00:45:07,971
birthdays and blood types.

835
00:45:08,038 --> 00:45:10,274
I create a character list first.

836
00:45:10,340 --> 00:45:12,943
Some people don't make these, but I do.

837
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:15,479
Mom probably doesn't make these.

838
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:17,548
She makes it up on the spot.
She's a Blood type O.

839
00:45:17,614 --> 00:45:20,384
So Aoi Minase is Type O, huh?

840
00:45:20,451 --> 00:45:22,986
Yeah. I'm an outsider, so I'm Type AB.

841
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:24,388
That makes sense.

842
00:45:24,455 --> 00:45:26,490
I'm Type A.

843
00:45:27,224 --> 00:45:29,460
Makes sense. You're a secret hard worker.

844
00:45:29,526 --> 00:45:31,595
That sounds like a dig!

845
00:45:31,662 --> 00:45:33,864
Sora! I'm going shopping!

846
00:45:33,931 --> 00:45:36,133
I'm getting wine to celebrate!

847
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:37,968
What are you celebrating?

848
00:45:39,269 --> 00:45:41,038
My proposal for the new novel
got accepted!

849
00:45:41,105 --> 00:45:43,474
Wow, congrats!

850
00:45:44,475 --> 00:45:46,176
Will you dance the happy dance?

851
00:45:46,243 --> 00:45:47,311
Yeah.

852
00:45:50,114 --> 00:45:51,215
Congrats!

853
00:45:51,949 --> 00:45:54,985
Congrats, congrats! Congrats, congrats!

854
00:45:55,052 --> 00:45:56,553
-Congrats, congrats.
-Can I join?

855
00:45:56,620 --> 00:45:58,255
-Congrats, congrats.
-Congrats.

856
00:45:58,322 --> 00:46:01,191
-Congrats, congrats, congrats.
-Congrats, congrats, congrats.

857
00:46:01,258 --> 00:46:04,361
-Thank you. Thank you.
-Congrats, congrats, congrats.

858
00:46:07,364 --> 00:46:10,634
<i>Let's play a throwback song next.</i>

859
00:46:12,136 --> 00:46:15,639
<i>Yoshiyuki Ohsawa's "So I Get Lost."</i>

860
00:46:21,311 --> 00:46:22,746
38.5 DEGREES CELSIUS

861
00:46:28,719 --> 00:46:31,188
I DON'T BELIEVE IT AT ALL,
BUT I DIAL THE NUMBER, HOPING…

862
00:46:35,392 --> 00:46:36,960
<i>I want to read this novel</i>

863
00:46:37,628 --> 00:46:39,229
<i>more than anyone!</i>

864
00:46:57,981 --> 00:47:01,919
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING. GOODBYE.

865
00:47:03,854 --> 00:47:04,988
What is this?

866
00:47:13,764 --> 00:47:17,201
BLOOD TYPE: AB

867
00:47:18,902 --> 00:47:19,736
Huh?

868
00:47:19,803 --> 00:47:21,738
I'm sure Mom doesn't make those.

869
00:47:21,805 --> 00:47:23,774
She makes it up on the spot.
She's Blood type O.

870
00:47:25,709 --> 00:47:28,045
I'm an outsider, so I'm Type AB.

871
00:47:49,299 --> 00:47:52,236
A Type O can't have a Type AB kid, right?

872
00:48:00,978 --> 00:48:01,845
<i>Hello?</i>

873
00:48:01,912 --> 00:48:04,047
It's me.

874
00:48:04,948 --> 00:48:06,717
<i>Did you see what I sent?</i>

875
00:48:08,485 --> 00:48:09,853
Yeah.

876
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:11,255
<i>So, it's goodbye.</i>

877
00:48:12,856 --> 00:48:14,524
I wasn't enough for you?

878
00:48:16,193 --> 00:48:17,261
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

879
00:48:25,369 --> 00:48:28,038
What will you do with your stuff?

880
00:48:29,039 --> 00:48:32,042
<i>Throw it out. I want everything to be new.</i>

881
00:48:38,081 --> 00:48:39,182
Including the men.

882
00:49:11,648 --> 00:49:12,816
AOI MINASE

883
00:49:12,883 --> 00:49:14,718
DIALING… AOI MINASE

884
00:50:00,330 --> 00:50:01,498
WE'LL SHOW YOU BEHIND THE SCENES OF DMD!

885
00:50:06,236 --> 00:50:08,538
-Shooting.
-Shooting.

886
00:50:08,605 --> 00:50:09,606
Start!

887
00:50:10,173 --> 00:50:11,508
Oh!

888
00:50:11,575 --> 00:50:12,609
Oh! I have my mask on!

889
00:50:34,398 --> 00:50:36,400
-<i>Become the wind</i>
-<i>Become the wind</i>

890
00:50:40,771 --> 00:50:42,005
-<i>Become…</i>
-<i>Become…</i>

891
00:50:50,647 --> 00:50:52,082
JADWIGA

892
00:51:01,625 --> 00:51:02,959
<i>She's not family?</i>

893
00:51:03,026 --> 00:51:04,094
<i>It's weird, right?</i>

894
00:51:04,161 --> 00:51:05,529
<i>Mom's Blood type O. I'm AB.</i>

895
00:51:05,595 --> 00:51:06,830
<i>Maybe you remembered wrong.</i>

896
00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:07,898
<i>I'm going to go check.</i>

897
00:51:07,964 --> 00:51:09,099
Don't let her test it!

898
00:51:09,166 --> 00:51:12,469
<i>I shouldn't have done the blood test!</i>

899
00:51:12,536 --> 00:51:13,437
<i>What should I do?</i>

900
00:51:13,503 --> 00:51:16,006
<i>Sora's leaving me. Sora's going away.</i>

901
00:51:16,073 --> 00:51:17,007
Subtitle translation by: Yukimi Ohashi

